Precipitation diminished overArgentina's summer crop areas in the week ended March 14, theU.S. Agriculture and Commerce Departments Joint WeatherFacility said.    In its International Weather and Crop Summary, the agencysaid crop areas in Cordoba, Santa Fe, and Buenos Aires receivedonly light scattered showers -- three to 13 millimeters.     The beneficial drier weather allowed drying of fields forsummer crop harvesting, following February's heavy rainfall, itsaid. Reuter&#3;